public static String getNamespaceURI(Node node) {
    if (node instanceof Document) {
        node = ((Document) node).getDocumentElement();
    }

    Element element = (Element) node; // This line might be problematic if node isn't an Element!

    String uri = element.getNamespaceURI();
    ...
}
```

The issue appears to be that this method assumes the node is an Element, but it could be other node types like TEXT, COMMENT, etc. This causes a ClassCastException in certain situations, particularly when processing the following axis.

